Just back up really close to the garage door and push the pedal.";i:36;s:65:"You should be able to see the brake lights illuminating the door.";i:37;s:75:"If even one of them comes on you know that the brake light fuse isnt blown.";i:38;s:38:"Well go into more depth on that below.";i:39;s:88:"Reconnect your machine to power then clear its memory and reprogram all remote controls.";i:40;s:82:"Unplug the device for a second time and reconnect the control wiring to the motor.";i:41;s:59:"Locate the wall mounted controls and disconnect the wiring.";i:42;s:74:"Use your garage door opener remote to test the functionality of your door.";i:43;s:43:"I figured it was key fob battery going bad.";i:44;s:87:"Recently its started taking a couple of times to turn the car on with the start button.";i:45;s:111:"And just yesterday the door unlock feature stopped working completely unless I manually pressed the fob button.";i:46;s:37:"So I replaced the battery in the fob.";i:47;s:51:"Now Ive gotten the car to turn over one time after.";i:48;s:56:"- Coding - Byte 23 Bit 5 Garage Door Opener installed 3.";i:49;s:178:"- Coding - Byte 6 Bit 6 Garage Opener installed After enabling these three bits the indicaor-lamp on the controller unit started working flashing when button 1 2 or 3 is pressed.";i:50;s:50:"But Garage door opener in MMI is still greyed out.";i:51;s:187:"Well if youve check the wiring harnesses of both the front right door and the rear right door and both seem to be in order then the next thing on the list would be the door module itself.";i:52;s:154:"Youll find that Audi did a very good job with windowdoor design and the module that communicates with the car and operates the window can be removed with.";i:53;s:101:"Well I have been workingrepairing the B5 clusters and changing the faulty LCD panels for a while now.";i:54;s:66:"I have also been involved with the B6B7 clusters and their issues.";i:55;s:95:"It appears that the main hardware issue on the B6B7 side has been that the speakerchime inside.";i:56;s:41:"You should hear the whirring of the pump.";i:57;s:70:"If there is no sound then it means the pump is not working in your Q7.";i:58;s:17:"No power to pump.";i:59;s:153:"If you do not hear whirring sound of the pump when you turn on the windshield washer system on your Audi Q7 you should first check the fuse for the pump.";i:60;s:64:"If the fuse is not blown check if the pump is getting any power.";i:61;s:96:"HomeLink can be programmed with up to three radio frequency codes for most current transmitters.";i:62;s:69:"To program HomeLink turn the ignition on but do not start the engine.";i:63;s:92:"Press and hold outside two buttons until the LED flashes then press and hold the button you.";i:64;s:50:"When inside the push button start is unresponsive.";}}